From 330bdccb90b90b96b7c86250cf0603d178354c68 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: emergent-agent-e1 <github@emergent.sh>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 16:52:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix SignalR client-side issues: registerSignalREvents
 structure, duplicate handlers, and UI restoration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Key fixes:
- Fixed registerSignalREvents() function structure - all handlers now properly inside
- Added connection.off() calls before all connection.on() to prevent duplicate handlers
- Removed duplicate code blocks (orphaned button code, duplicate escapeHtml function)
- Moved startGame() and addActivatedCard() functions outside registerSignalREvents()
- Fixed indentation throughout for consistency
- Ensured connection.start() is called only once
- Protected startGame() against duplicate clicks with isStartingGame flag
- Fixed RejoinSuccess handler to properly restore room state, host status, player cards
- Fixed RoomCreated handler to properly initialize UI after room creation
- ReceiveError handler now ignores harmless 'Гра вже запущена' messages

All SignalR event handlers now:
1. Use connection.off() before connection.on() to prevent duplicates
2. Are properly scoped inside registerSignalREvents()
3. Have consistent indentation
---
